posts.name: Bendix Diner
posts.note: Bendix Diner is an old-fashioned American diner with counter seating and a nostalgic vibe dishing up comfort classics.

posts.name: Bluestone Coffee Co
posts.note: Bluestone Coffee Co coffee is roasted on-site with light fare and desserts that are served till afternoon at this pleasant cafe. They are an unassuming café in the heart of Montclair, and they have one of the best brunches around.

posts.name: Cafe Angelique
posts.note: Cafe Angelique is a local cafe chain serving breakfast, sandwiches, and coffee drinks in a casual, stylish space. From their website, 'Cafe Angelique was founded in 2002 with its first location in NYC, and currently has four locations in New York City and New Jersey. The idea behind opening the café came from our love to gourmet coffee and high-quality pastries and food. Our Tenafly NJ location holds a live Jazz band weekly. (summer/ outdoor sitting area: Wednesday and Saturday, winter/ indoors: Wednesday).' NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Jammin’ Crepes
posts.note: Jammin’ Crepes has a counter-serve operation known for sweet, savory, and breakfast crêpes made with local ingredients. Need to order the Thanksgiving crepe and the 20 layer lemon crepe dessert.

posts.name: Hamburgao
posts.note: Hamburgao is a corner cafe for Brazilian-style burgers and casual comfort food in a no-frills space and the go to spot for Brazilian-style burgers in the Newark, NJ. NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Hot Dog Johnny's
posts.note: Hot Dog Johnny's is a longtime roadside hot dog stand with frosted glasses of buttermilk and birch beer plus a swing set. I have been told to get the chili dog.

posts.name: Piccini Wood Fired Brick Oven Pizza
posts.note: Piccini Wood Fired Brick Oven Pizza is a homey, cash-only eatery serving a wide-ranging menu of Italian staples, from pastas to sandwiches. Everyone orders the pizza which is great, but you need to get an order of pasta with meatballs and make sure to get another side of meatballs their that good.

posts.name: Razza
posts.note: Razza is an intimate pizzeria featuring artisan, wood-fired pies, and a bar with cocktails and Italian craft beer. They are challenging the common practices of pizza-making in the hope of influencing the industry and elevating the overall quality of pizza in America.

posts.name: Rossi's Bar And Grill
posts.note: Rossi's Bar And Grill serves hefty hamburgers, Italian pasta's, and cocktails in a classic tavern with nostalgic decor.

posts.name: Rutt’s Hut
posts.note: Rutt’s Hut is a cash-only, no-frills institution with a walk-up counter serving deep-fried hot dogs since 1928. Order the ripper hot dog with home-made relish.

posts.name: Skylark Diner and Lounge
posts.note: Skylark Diner and Lounge serves drinks and elevated comfort food in a funky, futuristic diner space. From their website, 'The Skylark Diner in Edison NJ has often been described as 'more than just a diner'. It’s a Bistro Casual Dining Restaurant for Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, and Late Night Snacks. It also has separate Bar Lounge with Unique Cocktails, a Notable Wine List, Craft Beers, and Bar Snacks. The Skylark Diner was Voted Best Diner in Central Jersey by readers of New Jersey Monthly Magazine for several years.'

posts.name: Smitty's Clam Bar
posts.note: Smitty's Clam Bar's a snug veteran clam shack preparing no-frills seafood dishes with a surfer vibe. You need to get one of their fried or baked seafood platters with an order of fries and cole slaw. If you're into clams they have great ones here, my friends swear by them.

posts.name: Tick Tock Diner
posts.note: Tick Tock Diner is an old-school 1940s art deco diner serving breakfast and American comfort food 24/7. In 2017 the Tick Tock Diner was named the second-best 24-Hour Diner in the nation by the Daily Meal.

posts.name: White Manna
posts.note: White Manna is a prominent, pint-sized burger joint draws crowds with its sliders, fries, and shakes. The White Mana is a historical landmark, as well as the first Manna to open and was the 1939 World's Fair building. When originally introduced, it was called the 'diner of the future' and an 'Introduction to Fast Food'.
